clip((xmin,ymin)--(xmin,ymax)--(xmax,ymax)--(xmax,ymin)--cycle);

[/asy] The area of the pentagon is the difference between the area of the rectangle and the four right triangles formed at the vertices of the rectangle. We find that \begin{align*}
A_1 &= \frac 12 \cdot 5 \cdot 2 = 5, \\
A_2 &= \frac 12 \cdot 4 \cdot 3 = 6, \\
A_3 &= \frac 12 \cdot 2 \cdot 5 = 5, \\
A_4 &= \frac 12 \cdot 3 \cdot 6 = 9,
\end{align*} while the area of the entire rectangle is $9 \times 8 = 72$. Thus, the area of the pentagon is equal to $72 -5 - 6 -5 - 9 = \boxed{47}$ square units.

