For what ordered pair $(a,b)$ are there infinite solutions $(x,y)$ to the system \begin{align*}
3ax+3y&=5b,\\
2x+y&=5.
\end{align*}

solution:
We can rephrase the problem as the system of equations: \begin{align*}
\frac{a+2b}{2} &= 7\\
\frac{a+2c}{2} &= 8
\end{align*} Adding these gives: \begin{align*}
\frac{a+2b}{2}+\frac{a+2c}{2} &= 7+8\\
\frac{2a+2b+2c}{2} &= 15\\
a+b+c &= 15\\
\frac{a+b+c}{3} &= \frac{15}{3} = \boxed{5}
\end{align*}

